The paper proposes a new formulation of Multiple-Instance Learning (MIL) and provides an efficient algorithm for it. MIL is a subfield of machine learning, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions Shapelet Learning for time-series classification, which falls under the subfield of Computer Vision (cs.CV). The use of shapelets and similarity measures suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper provides a theoretical analysis of the proposed approach, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the subfield of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
